HEADWORD: Morale
<hw>Mo`rale"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Moral</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>The moral condition, or the
condition in other respects, so far as it is affected by, or dependent
upon, moral considerations, such as zeal, spirit, hope, and confidence;
mental state, as of a body of men, an army, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

